'''Rokur Gepta's pets''' were a population of flying carnivores of an unknown [[Species/Legends|species]] kept by [[Rokur Gepta]] as pets. They were small, but could devour chunks of a [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]], as was often the case when Gepta wanted to dispose of the corpse of a subordinate who displeased him. They were covered in black hair or fur, shunned the light and had multiple legs; the exact number is unknown, but at least three. They had no head or face, but a pinkish, gummy aperture into which they took their food. They made their bed in grey-green muck. Aside from executed subordinates, he also fed them a [[Rokur Gepta's pet food|certain type of animal]].

